  "local_port": 33388,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can your remove white underarm stains from shirts?",
  "response": "Removing white underarm stains from shirts can be challenging, but several methods can help you get rid of them effectively. Here are some strategies:\n\n### 1. **Baking Soda Paste**\n- **Ingredients:** Baking soda and water.\n- **Method:** \n  1. Mix equal parts of baking soda and water to form a paste.\n  2. Apply the paste directly to the stained area.\n  3. Let it sit for about 30 minutes.\n  4. Scrub gently with a soft brush or cloth and then rinse with cold water before washing as usual.\n\n### 2. **White Vinegar**\n- **Ingredients:** White vinegar and water.\n- **Method:**\n  1. Mix one part white vinegar with two parts water.\n  2. Soak the stained area in the solution for about 30 minutes.\n  3. Rinse with cold water, then wash normally.\n\n### 3. **Lemon Juice and Baking Soda**\n- **Ingredients:** Lemon juice and baking soda.\n- **Method:**\n  1. Squeeze fresh lemon juice over the stained area.\n  2. Sprinkle baking soda on top of the lemon juice.\n  3. Let the mixture fizz and sit for about 30 minutes.\n  4. Rinse with cold water and launder as usual.\n\n### 4. **Hydrogen Peroxide**\n- **Ingredients:** Hydrogen peroxide (3%) and water.\n- **Method:**\n  1. Mix one part hydrogen peroxide with two parts water.\n  2. Soak the stained area in the solution for about 30 minutes.\n  3. Rinse thoroughly with cold water and wash as normal.\n\n### 5. **Dish Soap and Hydrogen Peroxide**\n- **Ingredients:** Dish soap, hydrogen peroxide, and baking soda.\n- **Method:**\n  1. Mix one cup hydrogen peroxide, one cup dish soap, and two tablespoons of baking soda.\n  2. Apply the mixture to the stain and gently scrub.\n  3. Let it sit for about 30 minutes.\n  4. Rinse with cold water and wash as usual.\n\n### 6. **Commercial Stain Removers**\n- Use a commercial stain remover designed for sweat stains. Follow the instructions on the product for the best results.\n\n### Additional Tips:\n- Always test any solution on a small, inconspicuous area of the fabric first to ensure it doesn't damage the material.\n- Avoid using hot water when rinsing, as it can set the stain.\n- Wash the shirt according to the care label instructions after treating the stain.\n- For heavily stained items, you may need to repeat the treatment process.\n\nBy using these methods, you should be able to effectively remove white underarm stains and keep your shirts looking fresh.",
